main event: An unidentified flying object was observed at high altitude for 30 minutes on February 28, 1961.
interesting points: The object was observed at an estimated altitude of 2700 feet and disappeared approximately 130 feet as it reached 15 feet elevation., The sighting lasted for 30 minutes., The object was possibly identified as a satellite or aircraft., No photographs were taken during the observation., The brightness of the object was compared to a first magnitude star.
